00:41:35.139 --> 00:41:36.765
Are you hurt?

00:41:36.849 --> 00:41:38.267
Are you hurt anywhere?

00:41:38.350 --> 00:41:39.268
No, I'm okay.

00:41:45.524 --> 00:41:47.651
I'm fine, but Mr. Gong is…

00:41:52.906 --> 00:41:54.867
Let's go. Come on.

00:41:55.618 --> 00:41:57.119
Okay, let's go.

00:41:57.202 --> 00:41:58.037
Easy, easy.

00:41:58.120 --> 00:41:59.204
Be careful.

00:42:01.040 --> 00:42:01.957
-Take my hand.
-Okay.

00:42:33.280 --> 00:42:34.907
What do you think you're doing?

00:42:50.130 --> 00:42:51.340
Ji-hyeok!

00:42:52.091 --> 00:42:53.425
They're over here!

00:43:09.316 --> 00:43:11.026
-Let's go.
-Okay.

00:43:11.694 --> 00:43:13.320
Slowly. Watch your step.

00:43:14.530 --> 00:43:15.406
Careful.

00:43:18.909 --> 00:43:19.743
Slowly.

00:43:20.869 --> 00:43:21.870
Slowly.

00:43:24.540 --> 00:43:25.374
Ji-hyeok!

00:43:26.083 --> 00:43:26.917
Ji-hyeok!

00:43:27.459 --> 00:43:28.961
Hey, Ji-hyeok!

00:43:29.044 --> 00:43:30.462
They're over here!

00:43:32.131 --> 00:43:33.090
Are you okay, Ms. Go?

00:43:33.799 --> 00:43:35.300
Ji-hyeok!

00:43:35.384 --> 00:43:36.301
Ji-hyeok!

00:43:37.094 --> 00:43:38.011
Are you okay?

00:43:40.139 --> 00:43:41.348
Do you know how worried I was?

00:43:42.141 --> 00:43:43.100
Can I get a towel?

00:43:43.809 --> 00:43:44.893
I can't believe this.

00:43:47.020 --> 00:43:48.605
Can I get something to cover him up with?

00:44:00.617 --> 00:44:01.577
Here.

00:44:03.036 --> 00:44:06.331
Mr. Kang picked it up.
He found it near where you fell.

00:44:06.415 --> 00:44:07.666
Right.

00:44:07.750 --> 00:44:09.001
I should thank him.

00:44:12.171 --> 00:44:13.005
Da-rim.

00:44:13.672 --> 00:44:14.548
Yeah?

00:44:15.132 --> 00:44:17.801
Why did Mr. Gong do that earlier?

00:44:17.885 --> 00:44:19.636
Even with me there,
he refused to let go of your hand.

00:44:22.848 --> 00:44:24.308
Maybe you should quit your job.

00:44:25.893 --> 00:44:27.978
Where did that come from?

00:44:28.061 --> 00:44:31.064
I'll take care of the hospital bills
and loan interest somehow.

00:44:31.148 --> 00:44:32.775
I can ask for an advance
on the photography exhibition.

00:44:33.609 --> 00:44:34.526
Why would you do that?

00:44:36.820 --> 00:44:37.696
What?

00:44:37.780 --> 00:44:39.656
Why would you go that far?

00:44:40.282 --> 00:44:41.784
I appreciate the thought,

00:44:42.367 --> 00:44:44.745
but I don't want to lose a friend
because I relied on them for money.

00:44:48.040 --> 00:44:50.167
And you're fine with relying on Mr. Gong?

00:44:56.089 --> 00:44:56.924
What?

00:44:57.007 --> 00:45:00.052
Think about how he paid off your debt
and what he did today.

00:45:00.135 --> 00:45:02.012
It looks to me like you and Mr. Gong

00:45:02.095 --> 00:45:04.515
are more than just a team leader
and a team member.

00:45:05.349 --> 00:45:07.351
I definitely think
he has feelings for you.

00:45:07.434 --> 00:45:08.560
It's nothing like that.

00:45:09.144 --> 00:45:11.021
He was delirious because he was sick.

00:45:11.104 --> 00:45:12.314
That's why he acted like that.

00:45:12.981 --> 00:45:13.857
That's why.

00:45:14.816 --> 00:45:15.651
Yeah.

00:45:32.209 --> 00:45:34.169
We should stop by the ER.

00:45:35.087 --> 00:45:36.797
Your face is so pale right now.

00:45:39.466 --> 00:45:40.801
I took medicine for the fever.

00:45:41.593 --> 00:45:42.469
I'm fine.

00:45:42.553 --> 00:45:44.012
I know, but still.

00:45:45.931 --> 00:45:47.432
I just want to go home.

00:45:49.226 --> 00:45:50.227
I want to rest.

00:46:32.603 --> 00:46:34.229
You're such a family man, Mr. Gong.

00:46:34.313 --> 00:46:36.315
You even come to look after your wife.

00:46:36.398 --> 00:46:39.109
Please, I'm just doing what's right.

00:46:39.192 --> 00:46:41.820
I wonder if this is even worth
writing an article about.

00:46:45.616 --> 00:46:47.200
This is it.

00:46:47.284 --> 00:46:48.535
Please come in.

00:46:50.245 --> 00:46:51.079
Honey.

00:47:00.088 --> 00:47:02.257
Did she go out for a walk?

00:47:02.841 --> 00:47:04.801
Go and look for her.
The reporter is waiting.

00:47:04.885 --> 00:47:06.261
Yes, sir.

00:47:14.728 --> 00:47:16.146
Does he have to take it today?

00:47:16.229 --> 00:47:17.606
He wants to release the photo of him
caring for his wife

00:47:17.689 --> 00:47:19.274
at the same time
as the new product launch.

00:47:19.358 --> 00:47:22.235
Jeez, did she really have to hide
and make our lives harder?

00:47:24.404 --> 00:47:26.782
-There she is. Over there.
-What?

00:47:33.955 --> 00:47:35.290
Go that way. Check the stairs.

00:47:42.547 --> 00:47:44.883
I'm Chairman Gong's secretary.
His wife is missing from the VIP room.

00:47:44.966 --> 00:47:46.385
Did she come this way by any chance?

00:47:46.468 --> 00:47:49.221
She was just in her room.
I'm not sure where she is.

00:47:49.763 --> 00:47:51.139
We need to find her right now.

00:47:51.223 --> 00:47:54.017
Please make an announcement
and contact security.

00:47:54.101 --> 00:47:55.477
Okay.

00:48:05.821 --> 00:48:07.030
Oh my gosh!

00:48:07.114 --> 00:48:08.657
-I'm sorry.
-Seriously?

00:48:09.366 --> 00:48:10.992
-Unbelievable.
-Ma'am, by any chance,

00:48:11.076 --> 00:48:13.120
did a woman with crutches come in here?

00:48:13.203 --> 00:48:14.705
-She did.
-Where is she?

00:48:15.539 --> 00:48:16.456
Right there and there.

00:48:17.124 --> 00:48:18.625
I'm the only one here without crutches.

00:48:18.709 --> 00:48:20.085
No, not those people.

00:48:20.168 --> 00:48:21.962
I wouldn't know about the patients
in the other rooms.

00:48:22.045 --> 00:48:23.213
I'm sorry.

00:48:23.296 --> 00:48:24.631
My goodness.

00:48:24.715 --> 00:48:26.466
He scared me half to death.

00:48:29.761 --> 00:48:30.971
He's gone.

00:48:31.054 --> 00:48:31.888
You can come out now.

00:48:32.806 --> 00:48:33.807
Thank you.

00:48:43.358 --> 00:48:45.485
Here. Drink this.

00:48:55.746 --> 00:48:57.372
Why were you hiding from him?

00:48:59.624 --> 00:49:00.709
Is he a loan shark?

00:49:02.794 --> 00:49:03.837
I'm being nosy again.

00:49:04.379 --> 00:49:05.297
I'm sorry.

00:49:08.216 --> 00:49:09.468
Thank you.

00:49:14.931 --> 00:49:16.308
It's fine.

00:49:17.100 --> 00:49:18.518
You're okay now.

00:49:19.227 --> 00:49:20.437
You're okay.

00:49:35.202 --> 00:49:37.746
Da-rim, how are you feeling?

00:49:38.288 --> 00:49:39.998
It's cold medicine.

00:49:40.081 --> 00:49:41.708
Dae-seong put you through
so much yesterday.

00:49:41.792 --> 00:49:43.418
I feel so terrible.

00:49:43.502 --> 00:49:45.921
It's all right. I'm fine.

00:49:46.004 --> 00:49:47.714
If I weren't, I wouldn't be at work.

00:49:47.798 --> 00:49:51.301
You should've taken the day off.
No one would've said anything.

00:49:51.927 --> 00:49:53.970
Take the medicine. You might have a cold.

00:49:54.054 --> 00:49:57.432
But still, you shouldn't skip payday.

00:49:57.516 --> 00:50:00.560
Our paychecks are in!

00:50:00.644 --> 00:50:01.937
-Oh my.
-Hurry up and check.

00:50:02.020 --> 00:50:04.397
-Really?
-Hurry.

00:50:04.481 --> 00:50:05.440
This is amazing.

00:50:06.149 --> 00:50:07.859
MS. GO DA-RIM'S SALARY ACCOUNT
2,270,000 WON

00:50:11.530 --> 00:50:12.531
Da-rim, are you crying?

00:50:12.614 --> 00:50:14.825
No, I'm not. Why would I be?

00:50:15.408 --> 00:50:16.743
I'm tearing up.

00:50:16.827 --> 00:50:18.411
I'm so touched.

00:50:19.496 --> 00:50:21.122
I mean, it'll all be gone later

00:50:21.206 --> 00:50:23.542
when I pay the overdue credit card bills
and loan payments,

00:50:23.625 --> 00:50:26.169
but I'm going to take it all in now
while I still can.

00:50:26.253 --> 00:50:27.087
You should.

00:50:27.170 --> 00:50:28.547
I'm going to buy myself something.

00:50:28.630 --> 00:50:30.423
I worked so hard this past month,

00:50:30.507 --> 00:50:32.384
so I deserve a nice treat.

00:50:32.467 --> 00:50:33.635
You mean multiple treats.

00:50:33.718 --> 00:50:35.178
Just look at all those packages.

00:50:35.262 --> 00:50:38.473
This time, I'm going to buy this.
Nan-suk, look.

00:50:38.557 --> 00:50:40.892
Is that seriously
meant to cover your body?

00:50:40.976 --> 00:50:44.062
Da-rim, look at this.
It'd look great on you. Buy it.

00:50:44.145 --> 00:50:45.272
I can't.

00:50:45.355 --> 00:50:47.649
I also have a lot of debt to pay off.

00:50:47.732 --> 00:50:49.192
You have loans too, huh?

00:50:49.734 --> 00:50:51.778
Then again, who doesn't?

00:50:54.406 --> 00:50:56.741
They gave us so much.

00:51:16.469 --> 00:51:18.263
It's the first payment, after all.

00:51:18.847 --> 00:51:21.057
Just giving him the money
doesn't feel right.

00:51:42.162 --> 00:51:42.996
Do you need something?

00:51:43.079 --> 00:51:46.166
Oh, it's nothing.

00:51:46.917 --> 00:51:49.044
Is Mr. Gong not in?

00:51:49.127 --> 00:51:50.170
He took a sick day.

00:51:50.253 --> 00:51:51.379
I think he has a bad cold.

00:51:52.380 --> 00:51:53.340
Oh, really?

00:51:54.090 --> 00:51:56.343
Is he feeling better now?

00:51:56.426 --> 00:51:59.596
He sounded pretty sick
when I called him earlier.

00:52:02.057 --> 00:52:04.768
Why do you ask?
Do you need something approved by him?

00:52:04.851 --> 00:52:06.770
No, I was just wondering.

00:52:20.659 --> 00:52:22.077
So that's what happened.

00:52:24.037 --> 00:52:24.996
Goodness me.

00:52:25.664 --> 00:52:28.208
How did you manage to endure
all those years?

00:52:29.334 --> 00:52:31.294
I didn't endure them.

00:52:33.046 --> 00:52:34.297
I just gave up.

00:52:36.299 --> 00:52:38.385
I was half out of my mind.

00:52:38.969 --> 00:52:40.679
I know it's not my place to say this,

00:52:41.304 --> 00:52:44.015
but you should've left with your son
and divorced your husband.

00:52:45.016 --> 00:52:46.059
My parents…

00:52:47.644 --> 00:52:50.313
were also relying on my husband.

00:52:52.357 --> 00:52:54.693
And the thought of living on my own…

00:52:56.987 --> 00:52:58.571
also scared me.

00:52:59.447 --> 00:53:00.323
I thought…

00:53:01.700 --> 00:53:03.410
if I just put up with it,

00:53:05.412 --> 00:53:06.538
everyone

00:53:07.580 --> 00:53:08.707
would be happy.

00:53:11.543 --> 00:53:12.460
"Happy"?

00:53:14.671 --> 00:53:15.964
Do you think

00:53:16.923 --> 00:53:21.261
your son was truly happy
watching you live like that?

00:53:23.430 --> 00:53:24.264
Pardon?

00:53:24.764 --> 00:53:27.726
They say that parents
are the whole world to their kids.

00:53:28.685 --> 00:53:29.894
When a parent falls apart,

00:53:30.729 --> 00:53:33.815
the child's whole world crumbles.

00:53:35.817 --> 00:53:37.360
He must've been so scared.

00:53:38.111 --> 00:53:40.905
We have to become braver

00:53:42.073 --> 00:53:43.616
and happier

00:53:44.409 --> 00:53:46.077
for our children's sake.

00:53:47.370 --> 00:53:48.872
That's what I think.

00:54:53.728 --> 00:54:55.814
Do you still resent me?

00:55:09.035 --> 00:55:10.495
It's been over 20 years.

00:55:10.578 --> 00:55:12.789
It's time for you to grow up already.

00:55:14.749 --> 00:55:15.917
Just because time has passed…

00:55:17.794 --> 00:55:19.420
doesn't mean it undoes what you've done.

00:55:20.463 --> 00:55:21.965
Are you blind to it all?

00:55:22.048 --> 00:55:23.675
My mom has lost her will to live.

00:55:24.259 --> 00:55:25.760
Your son doesn't believe in love.

00:55:26.594 --> 00:55:28.721
Don't you see the family you've destroyed?

00:55:32.100 --> 00:55:33.184
It was true love.

00:55:33.810 --> 00:55:35.311
I was just being true to my feelings.

00:55:38.148 --> 00:55:40.024
And people call that an affair.

00:55:40.775 --> 00:55:42.360
You know what disgusts me even more?

00:55:42.443 --> 00:55:44.779
Even after all that,
you hold your head high.

00:55:48.366 --> 00:55:50.618
You're talking
as if you're quite different from me.

00:55:50.702 --> 00:55:53.413
Then are you saying we're the same?

00:55:54.247 --> 00:55:55.790
Are you? How are we the same?

00:56:06.134 --> 00:56:06.968
Hey.

00:56:10.722 --> 00:56:13.183
You want that woman, don't you?

00:56:13.266 --> 00:56:14.684
You're dying to have her.

00:56:15.685 --> 00:56:18.521
You didn't even try to hide your feelings
in front of her husband.

00:56:20.106 --> 00:56:21.107
And you think…

00:56:23.026 --> 00:56:24.944
you have the right to criticize me?

00:56:29.282 --> 00:56:30.783
You and I are the same.

00:56:32.076 --> 00:56:33.077
Don't you see that?

00:57:27.590 --> 00:57:29.551
SEON-U

00:58:07.630 --> 00:58:09.048
I'm going to buy some meat on my way home.

00:58:09.132 --> 00:58:10.383
-Are you?
-What are you having for dinner?

00:58:10.466 --> 00:58:12.635
I want to spend some quality time
with my family.

00:58:12.719 --> 00:58:13.928
I should ask my kids.

00:58:14.012 --> 00:58:15.346
-All right.
-Bye, everyone.

00:58:15.430 --> 00:58:16.598
-Have a good night.
-Good night.

00:58:16.681 --> 00:58:17.682
-Get home safely.
-Have a nice evening.

00:58:17.765 --> 00:58:19.183
-Good job today.
-See you tomorrow.

00:58:22.395 --> 00:58:24.022
Excuse me, Mr. Kang.

00:58:24.105 --> 00:58:25.106
Yes, Ms. Go?

00:58:25.189 --> 00:58:28.192
Can I get Mr. Gong's address?

00:58:28.985 --> 00:58:29.819
What for?

00:58:30.403 --> 00:58:33.197
I can't help but think he got sick
because of me,

00:58:33.281 --> 00:58:35.617
so I thought I'd get him some porridge
on my way home.

00:58:39.954 --> 00:58:40.788
You're so thoughtful.

00:58:42.498 --> 00:58:43.458
One second.

00:59:21.079 --> 00:59:22.955
Did he go out somewhere?

00:59:46.979 --> 00:59:48.106
What are you doing here?

00:59:49.607 --> 00:59:52.902
I heard you were sick,
so I thought I'd bring you this.

00:59:52.985 --> 00:59:53.945
It's porridge.

00:59:54.821 --> 00:59:58.449
If you already had dinner,
you can heat it up and have it later.

00:59:58.533 --> 01:00:01.119
-If you put it in the fridge--
-How did you know where I live?

01:00:01.703 --> 01:00:04.372
It's incredibly rude
to show up unannounced.

01:00:06.624 --> 01:00:07.750
I'm sorry.

01:00:09.752 --> 01:00:11.921
I didn't call
because I didn't want to disturb you,

01:00:12.004 --> 01:00:13.423
but I did send you a text.

01:00:20.346 --> 01:00:21.514
I just thought…

01:00:22.974 --> 01:00:25.017
having someone check in on you
when you're sick

01:00:26.561 --> 01:00:30.189
could maybe provide some comfort
and strength.

01:00:34.026 --> 01:00:35.194
Does your husband…

01:00:37.488 --> 01:00:39.157
know you're here?

01:00:44.328 --> 01:00:45.163
Pardon?

01:00:45.246 --> 01:00:47.457
A man lives here alone.

01:00:48.958 --> 01:00:51.210
What would people say
if they saw you here?

01:00:53.004 --> 01:00:54.714
Don't cross the line.

01:00:59.844 --> 01:01:00.720
Wait.

01:01:00.803 --> 01:01:04.182
If you don't want the porridge,
there's also medicine…

01:01:05.475 --> 01:01:07.435
and this month's payment in here.

01:01:07.518 --> 01:01:09.145
Today was payday.

01:01:09.937 --> 01:01:11.397
That's also why

01:01:12.148 --> 01:01:15.526
I wanted to see you in person
and thank you.

01:01:15.610 --> 01:01:17.320
I had no other intentions.

01:01:19.906 --> 01:01:20.782
I'm sorry.

01:01:24.994 --> 01:01:27.413
I'll get going now.

01:01:51.354 --> 01:01:52.355
I'm…

01:01:52.939 --> 01:01:54.190
not a good person.

01:01:54.774 --> 01:01:55.608
Sorry?

01:01:57.610 --> 01:01:58.653
I'm also swayed.

01:02:03.366 --> 01:02:05.576
A man lives here alone.

01:02:07.119 --> 01:02:08.913
What would people say
if they saw you here?

01:02:08.996 --> 01:02:10.373
Don't cross the line.

01:03:21.319 --> 01:03:22.236
Ji-hyeok.

01:03:22.320 --> 01:03:23.863
What are you talking about?

01:03:26.657 --> 01:03:27.909
I want to get married

01:03:29.410 --> 01:03:30.536
as soon as possible.

01:03:58.105 --> 01:04:03.027
DYNAMITE KISS

01:04:33.140 --> 01:04:34.934
What are you doing?
Have you lost your mind?

01:04:35.017 --> 01:04:36.018
Is this because of Go Da-rim?

01:04:36.102 --> 01:04:37.103
You're the one who's lost your mind.

01:04:37.186 --> 01:04:38.646
Why do you make me worry?

01:04:38.729 --> 01:04:40.940
You always mess up,
get hurt, and fall ill.

01:04:41.023 --> 01:04:42.108
Can't you get your act together?

01:04:42.191 --> 01:04:44.902
I told you there was nothing between us.

01:04:44.986 --> 01:04:48.364
I just need to work as a team member
with him as the team leader. That's it.

01:04:48.447 --> 01:04:50.157
I'm a pro!

01:04:50.741 --> 01:04:51.742
It's okay.

01:04:51.826 --> 01:04:52.868
It's my job.

01:04:52.952 --> 01:04:54.704
You're here to make money,
not to play around.

01:04:55.246 --> 01:04:57.331
If something like this ever happens again,

01:04:57.415 --> 01:04:59.750
I'll kill you with my own hands.

01:04:59.834 --> 01:05:02.128
You don't know anything.
This is just a misunderstanding.

01:05:02.211 --> 01:05:03.212
A misunderstanding?

01:05:03.295 --> 01:05:06.007
Then tell me. What do I not know?

01:05:06.507 --> 01:05:10.928
Subtitle translation by: Justin S. Kim